ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>&#8220;On questio=
ns of strategy or ambition I ask &#8216;What would Sama do?&#8217;&#8221;</=
strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That combination of strategy and ambition is e=
ssentially grand strategy. And before Altman had achieved any success, Grah=
am singled him out for possessing it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The way to=
 view the past weekend isn&#8217;t as Altman pulling a good outcome from a =
bad situation in days.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s as the result =
of at least 15 years of building capabilities to match his aspirations, and=
 being adaptable enough to use them when the time came.</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><strong>Aligning Aspirations and Capabilities</strong></p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;"><span>The meta-principle from </span><em>On Grand Strategy </em><span>is=
 the importance of </span><strong>aligning your aspirations and your capabi=
lities.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If there&#8217;s just one thing=
 to take away, it&#8217;s that. So this is the one we&#8217;ll spend the mo=
st time on.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;Napoleon lost his empire by c=
onfusing aspirations with capabilities;&#8221; Gaddis writes. &#8220;Lincol=
n saved his country by not doing so.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><spa=
n>Time, space, and scale. Napoleon lost his empire by failing to align his =
capabilities with the </span><strong>scale</strong><span> of the challenge =
in Russia. Lincoln saved his by patiently waiting for the right </span><str=
ong>time</strong><em><strong> </strong></em><span>to issue the Emancipation=
 Proclamation.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Octavian, who would =
become Caesar Augustus, grew his capabilities over </span><strong>time</str=
ong><span> to match his aspirations as well.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">After the death of Julius Caesar in 44 BC, his heir Octavian waited 17 =
years to claim the leadership of the Roman Republic that Caesar passed to h=
