e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Altman played the situatio=
n perfectly. He drew on a career&#8217;s worth of built-up capabilities and=
 relationships, and maintained flexibility on the specifics in pursuit of t=
he long-term goal by showing a willingness to work towards AGI at a new sta=
rtup, within Microsoft, or at OpenAI.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It was dow=
nright Octavian.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When Octavian reached the heigh=
t of his power after the downfall of his rival Antony, writes Gaddis:&#160;=
</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; pa=
dding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>He secured authority by=
 appearing to renounce it, most dramatically on the first day of 27 when he=
 unexpectedly gave up all his responsibilities. The surprised senate had no=
 choice but to forbid this and to award Octavian the title of princeps (&#8=
220;first citizen&#8221;) &#8211; as well as a new name: Augustus.</em></p>=
</blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The board, meanwhile, failed miserably in it=
s coup by ignoring the lessons of grand strategy.&#160;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>As Gaddis warns, &#8220;The principle, for both Augustine and Machi=
avelli, reflects common sense: </span><strong>if you have to use force, don=
&#8217;t destroy what you&#8217;re trying to preserve.&#8221;</strong><span=
>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">They almost destroyed the company, and =
ended up destroying their oversight over it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Why=
?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Their </span><strong>capabilities didn&#=
8217;t match their aspirations</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">In fact, they seemed to have wildly misjudged their capabilities, bel=
ieving that the company&#8217;s wonky governance structure gave them the le=
eway to do as they wished, but not realizing that real power doesn&#8217;t =
come from pieces of paper, but from the will of the people.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">They didn&#8217;t realize that OpenAI is nothing without its pe=
ople.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And they didn&#8217;t maintain </spa=
n><strong>ecological sensitivity</strong><span>. They didn&#8217;t understa=
nd the tech community well enough to understand that most people would supp=
ort Altman, didn&#8217;t understand the investors well enough to know how m=
uch pressure they would apply, and didn&#8217;t know the company well enoug=
h to realize that its people would walk. They didn&#8217;t pick up on the s=
ubtle vibe shift from safetyism to acceleration, and failed to anticipate h=
ow little support they would receive.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The=
y came at the king, and missed, and made him the Emperor.&#160;&#160;</p><h=
3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-appearance: optimizeleg=
ibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: optimize=
