m; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; positio=
n: relative;"><strong>Becoming a Grand Strategist</strong></h3><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">Here&#8217;s the thing: as crazy as this past week was, things are go=
ing to keep getting crazier.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>I keep bangin=
g this drum, but I can&#8217;t bang it loudly enough: </span><strong>things=
 will keep getting crazier</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><spa=
n>The things that tech companies build in the coming years will blow even m=
y optimistic mind and give them power on a scale no company has had. They&#=
8217;ll rival nation-states. They </span><em>already</em><span> rival natio=
n-states &#8211; Apple&#8217;s $383 billion in 2023 revenue would rank it 4=
1st in the world in national GDP, sandwiched between Hong Kong and South Af=
rica, and while revenue and GDP aren&#8217;t perfect comps, those are serio=
us numbers &#8211; but they&#8217;ll rival more powerful ones.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Battles like one we all just witnessed at OpenAI, lik=
e the decades-long attack on nuclear, like the government&#8217;s anti-cryp=
to Operation Chokepoint 2.0, will become more common, not less.&#160;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">And that&#8217;s fair. The stakes are that high.&#160;</p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If you&#8217;re reading this and you have ambitions =
to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/59ebe63a-0864-4a68-8748-=
e7c2152fa6c1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">mak=
e the world a different place</a><span>, know that coming in, but don&#8217=
;t let it deter you. Know that it&#8217;s what you&#8217;re up against, and=
 start crafting your own grand strategy.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Acquire capabilities to match your ambitions. Maintain ecological sensitivi=
ty. Build alliances. Embrace chaos. Know theory while accepting that it won=
&#8217;t survive contact with practice. Remain flexible in tactics and stea=
dfast in ambition.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Certainly, read </span>=
<em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/1f4c6338-bec4-49f1-a284-630486=
185fc0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" =
rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">On Grand =
Strategy</a></em><span>. I captured a fraction of the lessons from the book=
=2E Live in the stories that Gaddis tel=
ls, put yourself in the shoes of histo=
ry&#8217;s greats.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Coming up on the=
 holiday season, when we all get a little time to relax and reflect, think =
about the final theme from the book: </span><strong>Know What It&#8217;s Al=
l About</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">What are you working to=
wards, and why?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There&#8217;s never been a bette=
r time for a small group of passionate people to change the course of histo=
ry, for the better, bloodlessly. Go craft your grand strategy and get to wo=
rk.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"back=
